This paper belongs to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) field, which is a subfield of Computer Science. The paper presents a tool for personality recognition from unstructured text, which involves techniques such as instance-based classification and feature extraction. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as unsupervised learning and classification, which are covered by sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category, as the paper involves extracting relevant features from text to classify personality types. 

Finally, the paper also involves aspects of Cybernetics (cs.CY), which covers the study of communication and control in complex systems, including human behavior.
